"{\"abstract\":\"We propose a general method for generating counterfactual explanations (CFXs) for a range of Bayesian Network Classifiers (BCs), e.g. singleor multi-label, binary or multidimensional. We focus on explanations built from relations of (critical and potential) influence between variables, indicating the reasons for classifications, rather than any probabilistic information. We show by means of a theoretical analysis of CFXs\\u2019 properties that they serve the purpose of indicating (potentially) pivotal factors in the classification process, whose absence would give rise to different classifications. We then prove empirically for various BCs that CFXs provide useful information in real world settings, e.g. when race plays a part in parole violation prediction, and show that they have inherent advantages over existing explanation methods in the literature.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"1810684853\",\"name\":\"Emanuele Albini\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1810684853\"},{\"authorId\":\"1911563\",\"name\":\"Antonio Rago\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1911563\"},{\"authorId\":\"1710592\",\"name\":\"P. Baroni\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1710592\"},{\"authorId\":\"143719014\",\"name\":\"F. Toni\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/143719014\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":null,\"name\":\"Kristijonas \\u010cyras\"},{\"authorId\":null,\"name\":\"Tiago Oliveira\"},{\"authorId\":null,\"name\":\"Amin Karamlou\"},{\"authorId\":null,\"name\":\"Francesca Toni\"}],\"doi\":\"10.3233/aac-200523\",\"intent\":[],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"0dba51332e7d74fda431566d4e69ac9c42cd1610\",\"title\":\"Assumption-based argumentation with preferences and goals for patient-centric reasoning with interacting clinical guidelines\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/0dba51332e7d74fda431566d4e69ac9c42cd1610\",\"ven